@startuml
title UML Component - Current Monorepo Modules and Runtime Dependencies

skinparam componentStyle rectangle
left to right direction

actor "Investor" as Investor
actor "API Consumer" as ApiConsumer

package "apps" {
  [apps/ui\nReact/Vite client] <<module>> as UI
  [apps/api\nFastAPI application] <<module>> as API
}

package "ml" {
  [ml/model\ntraining + inference code] <<module>> as MLModel
  [ml/artifacts\njoblib model bundles] <<storage>> as MLArtifacts
  [ml/data/raw\ndataset inputs] <<storage>> as MLData
  [ml/reports\ntraining outputs] <<storage>> as MLReports
}

package "shared" {
  [shared/db\nSQLAlchemy engine + ORM models] <<module>> as SharedDB
  [shared/auth\npassword hashing helpers] <<module>> as SharedAuth
}

package "services" {
  [services/data_migrator\nbootstrap + CSV import] <<service>> as Migrator
}

package "root compatibility layer" {
  [api.py] <<entrypoint>> as RootApi
  [main.py] <<entrypoint>> as RootMain
  [inference.py,\ntrain.py,\npreprocessing.py,\ndata_loading.py,\nevaluate.py,\nutils.py] <<entrypoint>> as RootML
}

database "PostgreSQL" as Postgres
[office-sale.csv] <<data source>> as CsvSource

Investor --> UI : uses
ApiConsumer --> API : calls /predict and /predict/batch
UI --> API : calls /auth, /opportunities,\n/shortlist over HTTP

RootApi ..> API : compatibility import / uvicorn entrypoint
RootMain ..> MLModel : compatibility training entrypoint
RootML ..> MLModel : compatibility re-export layer

API ..> MLModel : uses inference and preprocessing
API ..> MLArtifacts : reads best_model.joblib
API ..> SharedDB : uses SessionLocal and ORM models
API ..> SharedAuth : verifies passwords
API --> Postgres : reads users, listings,\nvaluations, shortlist_items

MLModel ..> MLArtifacts : writes and reads model bundles
MLModel ..> MLData : reads dataset
MLModel ..> MLReports : writes reports and shortlist outputs

Migrator ..> SharedDB : uses engine and sessions
Migrator ..> API : calls ensure_listing_valuations()
Migrator ..> CsvSource : imports source listings
Migrator --> Postgres : runs migrations and imports seed data
@enduml
